cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, specifically about frame induction. The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a probabilistic approach to frame induction. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with machine learning and natural language processing. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with information extraction from text. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper proposes a novel application of a split-merge method from syntactic parsing.
